    "body": "From, https://github.com/cython/cython/blob/ee1b02191853e40a0078114c29de5cf7d794ba66/Cython/Distutils/old_build_ext.py#L87-L89 Cython's `build_ext` starts using and modifying distutils' options attributes directly instead of making a copy of them.\r\n\r\nIf using setuptools' `setup` function (most likely the case) and Cython is installed then setuptools will successfully (and unconditionally) [import Cython's `build_ext`](https://github.com/pypa/setuptools/blob/af4e065b58789fd67fdbc897af981b670f01099b/setuptools/command/build_ext.py#L17), therefore Cython's modifications to these lists do happen and is, more than anything, confusing whenever using directly or subclassing distutils' `build_ext` that these options appear out of \"nowhere\".",
